The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 29 January is 35,684 (4,130.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 24 January, there were 2,830 new confirmed cases (327.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 January, there were 4,251 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 33% (1,421 fewer cases).
